    <sharedRules>
        <rule name="Gauss" id="5964-7270-0ed0-46b3" hidden="false">
            <description>To wound rolls of 5+ always wound the target and inflict an automatic glancing hit with AT(1) on vehicles unless the armor penetration is already sufficient for a penetrating hit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Tesla" id="a46e-c5c8-0256-4fc9" hidden="false">
            <description>To hit rolls of 5+ are always successful and the target suffers 2 additional automatic hits.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Reanimation Protocols" id="19cf-5493-0614-4436" hidden="false">
            <description>The army receives 3 Reanimation Points (RPoints) for every 500 points of game size. These points can be used to heal wounded or fallen models.
During the Reinforcement phase, each unit must be allocated at least as many RPoints with this rule as the number of wounds it has lost so far (including slain models).
If the RPoints are not enough for all models, the player can decide which units receive the RPoints.
A unit can only gain more RPoints than lost wounds if there is no other unit that has not yet gained as many RPoints as it has lost wounds.
Roll one die for every RPoint. On a 4+, the unit regains one wound and the RPoint is retained for the upcoming Reinforcement phase. Damaged models have to be healed up first before any slain model can return to the unit.
On a 3, the unit gains no wound and the RPoint is retained for the upcoming Reinforcement phase.
On a 1 or 2, the unit gains no wound and the RPoint is lost for the rest of the game.
If a unit has been completely wiped out, leave the last model on the field until the next Reinfocement phase, where it may be revived with RPoints. Such units take a -1 penalty on the roll. If the unit is not revived (either because no roll was successful or no attempt was made), it is permanently removed from play.
Slain models that are restored with RPoints have to be placed into direct base contact with as many of the remaining models of the unit as possible. Unless the unit is still engaged with an enemy in melee, they may not be placed in direct base contact with an enemy model (and only with models that their unit is already engaged with).
If the unit was completely killed, put them as close as possible to their last position into direction to their own deployment zone, outside of base contact with enemy models. 
Some units are able to gain "temporary RPoints". These RPoints are resolved normally as described above, but will be discarded automatically at the end of the current battle round and have no effect on the remaining RPoint pool of the player.
If a model is killed by a weapon that has at least twice the Strength of its own Toughness, it cannot use Reanimation Protocols.
For rules like "Blood Tithe" and "Power through Pain", a unit is only considered eliminated when it can no longer use RP, or no models make or succeed in their RP rolls in the upcoming Reinforcement phase. If it is the last round of a game, the unit is considered destroyed when it loses its last wound.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Experimental Rules" id="6bee-41ef-6bf5-4e49" hidden="false">
            <description></description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Any rule presented here is currently undergoing playtesting and is completely optional for you to use in your games. Changes are marked in red." id="be0c-219a-596e-4f6e" hidden="false">
            <description></description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Reanimation Protocols experimental" id="6826-995f-c4ef-41f3" hidden="false">
            <description>During the Reinforcement phase, living models with this rule regain all of their lost wounds. 
Additionally, roll 1D6 for each lost Wound on a model that was slain in the previous battle round.
- For each result of 5+, the unit restores one lost Wound. Damaged models must be fully healed before any other slain model can return to the unit.
- Any model that can't regain at least one Wound is permanently destroyed and cannot attempt further rolls.
Restored models must be placed in base-to-base contact with as many models of their unit as possible. They may not be placed in contact with enemy models unless the unit is already engaged in melee (and only with models that their unit is already engaged with).
If a destroyed unit is restored via Reanimation Protocols, the models are placed as close as possible to the last that was removed from that unit, outside of melee range with any enemy.
For the purposes of abilities such as Blood Tithe or Power through Pain, a unit is only considered destroyed if no models succeed in their Reanimation Protocol rolls in the upcoming Reinforcement phase.
If it is the final battle round, a unit is considered destroyed immediately when it loses its last Wound.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Royal Court Crypteks" id="f266-a75c-e0cc-47df" hidden="false">
            <description>If an Overlord is present, up to four Crypteks can be chosen that do not occupy an HQ slot. If a Lord is present, up to two Crypteks can be chosen that do not occupy an HQ slot.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Chronomancer" id="93ee-96ec-9e30-49c5" hidden="false">
            <description>Rites of Time - A Chronometron additionally grants +1 Initiative to the model and its attached unit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Dynasty Scion" id="a32e-7b9d-5f8f-43ef" hidden="false">
            <description>Heir to the Dynasty - The model gains an improved profile (see above) and has access to $Lord$ equipment in the Armory, instead of $Cryptek$.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Plasmancer" id="842e-230b-99a9-4989" hidden="false">
            <description>Rites of the Storm - Automatic wounds caused by equipment from this model trigger on a 3+.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Psychomancer" id="73cb-d96f-b878-409e" hidden="false">
            <description>Rites of Horror - Once per turn, an enemy unit within 18" suffers a cumulative -1 penalty to its Leadership until the next Rally phase.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Technomancer" id="9fc5-94c3-3fe4-49b7" hidden="false">
            <description>Rites of Reanimation - Once per turn, one Reanimation Protocol roll for a unit within 6" is automatically successfull.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Royal Court Lords" id="aeb9-77be-707c-45c4" hidden="false">
            <description>If an Overlord is present, up to four Lords can be chosen that do not occupy an HQ slot.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Royal Necrodermis" id="8453-b21a-c75b-426f" hidden="false">
            <description>Reduces AP of enemy attacks by -1 (to a minimum of 0).</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Royal Court Wardens" id="16dc-d82a-81d8-43cc" hidden="false">
            <description>If an Overlord is present, up to four Royal Wardens can be chosen that do not occupy an HQ slot. If a Lord is present, up to two Royal Wardens can be chosen that do not occupy an HQ slot.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Relentless March" id="49c6-610c-dd90-4dfc" hidden="false">
            <description>The model and its attached unit may shoot “Rapid fire” weapons at full range with a "Move & Shoot" order and ignores the to hit penalty for "Advance" orders with "Assault" weapons.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="CTan Necrodermis" id="dfa9-7a3c-caa2-4ea2" hidden="false">
            <description>The model has a 4+ invulnerability save. If it loses its last wound, it explodes like a vehicle.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Powers of the Ctan" id="fa41-afba-c732-4c36" hidden="false">
            <description>The model can manifest 2 powers per turn automatically. It knows all the powers from the list of Ctan powers. Each Ctan can only use each power once per battle round.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Great Illusion" id="7c10-b9b5-b9fc-4ae8" hidden="false">
            <description>At the beginning of the first battle round, the Deceiver can remove up to three units from his own army from the field and relocate them within his own deployment zone. Alternatively, each unit can also be placed in reserve.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Containment field" id="7bc4-fa71-6fce-46e5" hidden="false">
            <description>The model has a 5+ invulnerability save.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Living metal" id="dfed-be19-c20d-4c84" hidden="false">
            <description>The model repairs one vehicle damage at the start of each Reinforcement phase in any order.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Nanoscarab reanimator beam" id="1d61-a015-df01-45e5" hidden="false">
            <description>Instead of using the Atomiser beam, you may target a friendly $Necron$ unit within 12". The target immediately succeeds at 2 Reanimation Protocol rolls.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Dark prison" id="2f25-41ff-a3e5-40f4" hidden="false">
            <description>The model can dispel 1 psychic power per battle round.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Fabricator claw array" id="7348-17b3-702b-4e65" hidden="false">
            <description>At the end of its movement, the model can attempt to repair a vehicle within 3". On a 4+, an "Immobilized" or "Weapon Destroyed" result is removed from the vehicle, or 1 hull point is restored.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Scarab hive" id="67d1-b04f-d4b1-458d" hidden="false">
            <description>At the end of its movement, the model can repair up to 3 points of damage to a unit of Canoptek Scarabs within 3". Slain models can be revived with this ability if at least a single Canoptek Scarab model from its unit is still alive.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Servant" id="768f-279d-c12e-4c0b" hidden="false">
            <description>The unit cannot contest or hold mission objectives.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Systematic Vigour" id="5d9d-ee76-52cf-4c54" hidden="false">
            <description>If a Cryptek is attached to the unit, each Technothrall gains a bonus of +1 on to hit rolls. Technothralls do not prevent a Cryptek from joining another unit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Aetheric Interception" id="7667-ce4c-d5a0-4eea" hidden="false">
            <description>Deathmarks roll two dice less for scatter when deep striking. Additionally, once an enemy unit emerges from reserve, a Deathmark unit that has not yet used its order this round of combat may perform an intercept. The Deathmark unit is removed from the field or from reserves and immediately deployed within 18" of the enemy reserve unit. The Deathmarks can then fire at that unit as if it had been given the "Move & Shoot" order. The attack resolves after the enemy unit has been deployed and before it takes another action.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Royal Assassin" id="e9a8-84bb-3fac-4d50" hidden="false">
            <description>For each Lord or Skorpekh Lord, a Hexmark Destructor can be chosen that does not occupy an elite slot.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Dispersion shield" id="3eac-8a13-9697-45a0" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains a 5+ invulnerability save and the abilities "Deflect" and "Parry".</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Varguard" id="c033-0a3b-1629-4b4e" hidden="false">
            <description>If a single Lychguard model is selected, it becomes a character model.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Psionic Abomination" id="4457-d60d-1273-4ad3" hidden="false">
            <description>The unit can never be targeted by psychic powers. Enemy psykers within 18" suffer a -1 penalty on any roll to manifest and dispel psychic powers. Enemy units within 12" suffer a -1 penalty to their Leadership. All ranged and melee attacks made by the unit against a target within 6" gain "Shield breaker(-1)".</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Infused Madness" id="3768-9b96-36f8-4555" hidden="false">
            <description>At the start of any activation, roll 1D6 for each model in the unit that the Plasmacyte has joined. On each 1 or 2, the unit suffers one Mortal Wound. Models killed by this ability are removed from play and Reanimation Protocols cannot be used. All surviving models gain the special rules "Decimate", "Lance(1)" and "Quick(1)" for melee attacks until the start of their next activation. A Plasmacyte receives the same movement and deployment rules as the unit it joins. Can only affect $Necron$ units. Each Plasmacyte may use this ability once per game.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Quantum shielding" id="f6c6-7e24-4446-4206" hidden="false">
            <description>The model increases its armor values by +2 on each side, up to a maximum of 14. If it suffers a penetrating hit that is not prevented by a saving throw, it loses these bonuses until the next Reinforcement phase.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Targeting relay" id="977a-f8d0-33c9-4838" hidden="false">
            <description>After scoring a hit on an enemy unit, the next friendly unit firing on the same target can re-roll one failed to hit and wound roll.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Reinforced forelimbs" id="530f-b985-0414-4667" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains +3 to WS and +2 A.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Explosion" id="2821-4177-1e63-40aa" hidden="false">
            <description>Scarab swarms may explode at the end of their movement. For each base remaining, an enemy unit within 3" suffers a hit with S 5 AP 0 D 1; Explosive. All Scarab swarms in the unit are removed after the explosion.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Bloodswarm Scarabs" id="469a-96a2-8a0a-4ba9" hidden="false">
            <description>Flayed Ones that deep strike within 6" do not scatter.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Flensing Scarabs" id="acf2-35f6-e375-41b7" hidden="false">
            <description>Melee attacks gain "Poison(2+)".</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Frenzied Scarabs" id="3201-9e78-fc2b-49be" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains +1 Initiative.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Whip coils" id="a82d-48ea-b566-4921" hidden="false">
            <description>Enemy models in base contact get -1 attack in close combat, to a minimum of 1. Stacks with itself.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Wraith form" id="4fb0-9614-4bc5-4570" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains a 4+ invulnerability save.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Tunneling Horrors" id="df99-945a-fe5a-4a2e" hidden="false">
            <description>Once per game, at the start of their activation, the unit may use a Stand & Shoot order to be immediately re-deployed anywhere on the battlefield. They must keep a minimum distance of 6" to enemy models.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Nebuloscope" id="a7fc-a85c-e4f4-4c7b" hidden="false">
            <description>Ranged attacks gain "Seeking".</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Shadowloom and shieldvanes" id="a234-a9ab-198a-4609" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains a 3+ armor save and a  5+ invulnerability save.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Sentinel construct" id="815e-581d-03be-4ef8" hidden="false">
            <description>If a friendly unit is charged within 12", the Dominator Strider can also fire Overwatch.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Power surge" id="c81a-1555-af38-4864" hidden="false">
            <description>The Doomsday cannon's "High energy" profile may only be used with a "Stand & Shoot" command.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Gate of Eternity" id="aa42-98e2-1282-485c" hidden="false">
            <description>Instead of using its particle whip, a Monolith can teleport a friendly $Necron$ unit to it. Remove the target unit from the battlefield and redeploy it within 3" of the Monolith.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Lumbering" id="cb2c-6ddd-235b-404b" hidden="false">
            <description>The model can never move more than 6". If it arrives via Deep strike from reserve and would land on top of an enemy unit, move all models as little as possible to make room for the Monolith.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Chariot" id="ef82-6b90-8843-47b2" hidden="false">
            <description>The Overlord is transported by the Catacomb Command Barge (CCB) and can leave it at any time. No other model may be transported by the CCB. The Overlord can fight normally in melee while being embarked in the CCB.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Repair Barge" id="0261-d226-35c7-4118" hidden="false">
            <description>During the Reinforcement Phase, you may target up to three units that are either within 3" of it or are on board as passengers. Each unit automatically succeeds at 1 Reanimation Protocol roll. The same unit can be targeted multiple times.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Transport" id="02d1-9e4a-7267-467e" hidden="false">
            <description>This model has a transport capacity of 12 models. If the model is destroyed, passengers do not suffer damage, but are placed in reserve. They will automatically appear via Deep strike the next time they activate. Passengers may disembark even if the model is not in hover mode.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Activation" id="3b8c-7a2c-c298-4ad2" hidden="false">
            <description>All Starsteles start the game deactivated. They can be activated by holding them like a mission objective at the end of the battle round. If an active Starstele is hold like a mission objective, it may instead activate an inactive one.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Buried in the earth" id="557d-9729-adb9-49db" hidden="false">
            <description>After all units (including infiltrators) have been set up, deploy all Starsteles from your army. Set them up via Deep strike rules outside the enemies deployment zone. The unit always scatters, even if a "hit" is rolled for the scatter die (follow the small arrow on it for direction) and can never stray closer than 1" to another unit, terrain, the enemies deployment zone or the edge of the field. Reduce the deviation only enough to place the model.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Dolmen gate network" id="3baf-4d2f-d2b3-439c" hidden="false">
            <description>All of your active Startsteles are connected and act like a transport vehicle (with the same restrictions in regards to which passengers may use it). This means a unit may embark in one active Starstele and disembark in another the next turn. Each Starstele may only be used once per battle round to either have a unit embark on it, or disembark from it. The Starstele always counts as having moved 6". Units arriving from reserves may exit from a Starstele instead of other deployment methods, if they could embark on it in the first place.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Inactive" id="006b-02bf-fb36-40ed" hidden="false">
            <description>The model may only be targeted by the enemy after it has been activated.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Mark of Dominion" id="560a-5922-6d21-4562" hidden="false">
            <description>Enemy models within 12" of an inactive Starstele receive a -1 penalty to manifest a psychic power. If the Starstele is active, the penalty increases to -2.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Unmanned" id="9aae-7cbd-3ab5-b7b9" hidden="false">
            <description>A Starstele can't contest or capture mission objectives.</description>
        </rule>
    </sharedRules>
    <sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
    </sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
    <categoryEntries>
    </categoryEntries>
    <catalogueLinks>
    </catalogueLinks>
</catalogue>